    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Ctrl-M now switches you to 'command mode', where you can't type text directly in cells. From command mode, you can hit enter to go into edit mode. We're still discussing whether inserting a new cell should enter edit mode or not - the main argument against is that you often want to change the cell type before you start typing.\n"
